race.comment: Tricky contest to end the day. OHTANI (11) doesn't win out of turn but drops six kilos in weight for this fourth-up. Ran on late with an encouraging fourth over this trip at Goulburn. Can race a little closer to the speed and score a long overdue victory. LUNA BAY (7) improving filly heading in the right direction. Bounced off her excellent debut second with a gritty maiden win over 1500m at Kembla Grange. Expected to give a great sight again despite drawing out. PERFECT JUSTICE (1) two runs back have been full of merit and the visors come off today. Taken to the front when holding on for a sound fourth over 1600m at this track. Molly Bourke sticks and he gets a much better set-up today. Genuine top-three player. CHANNELLING (5) has sound figures on her home track and relished the mile for the first time when a tenacious second at this track. Has an awkward gate to deal with and place prospects look best.
